Osmia laticeps
Thomson 1872: 242
[Lectotype female: Lund]; 
Dalla Torre 1896: 414
[synonymy with 
Osmia uncinata
Gerstaecker
]; 

Tkalcu
1983: 154

[Lectotype designation]; 
Nilsson 2009: 51
[rejection of synonymy with 
Osmia uncinata
Gerstaecker
].

In the Nearctic, Osmia laticeps is known from Yukon east to Nova Scotia, and as far south as Ontario and Michigan. In the Palearctic, Osmia laticeps is known from Germany northwest to Sweden and Finland, east to Latvia and northern Siberian Russia (
Mueller 2010
).
